cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use REACH or OCTO in your work, please cite as below."
type: software
title: "REACH + OCTO: A Local Workflow Practice and Orchestration Pattern"
abstract: >
  REACH is a local workflow practice where Claude authors single-file C# scripts
  on demand, reaching into live systems via a declarative intent DSL. OCTO is an
  orchestration layer built on REACH — multiple arms reach simultaneously, findings
  combine into a contextual decision surface, and human judgment is a first-class
  architectural primitive.
authors:
